   Many dealers fight tooth and nail to get space in the upper lots,
believing that the lower one (on Bonnie Avenue) is akin to Siberia
for their goods. Truth is, the college has a lot of ground to cover,
and some shoppers run out of steam before getting to the lower level;
some don't even know it's there.

